# Milutin Theme - Coding Standards

## General Rules
- Use 2 spaces for indentation
- No trailing whitespace
- Files end with a single newline
- UTF-8 encoding only

## Liquid
- Use `{% liquid %}` tag for multiple statements
- Prefer `{{ variable | default: 'fallback' }}` over conditionals
- Always escape user content with `| escape`
- Use meaningful variable names
- Comment complex logic with `{% comment %}{% endcomment %}`

## CSS
- Mobile-first approach
- BEM naming: `.block__element--modifier`
- Use CSS custom properties for theming
- No `!important` unless absolutely necessary
- Group properties: positioning, box model, typography, visual
- Max selector specificity: 3 levels

## JavaScript
- Vanilla ES6+ only, no jQuery
- Use `const` by default, `let` when needed, never `var`
- Async/await over promises where applicable
- Document public methods with JSDoc
- Use custom events for component communication
- Debounce scroll/resize handlers

## SVG Icons
- Inline SVG in snippets
- Include `aria-hidden="true"` for decorative icons
- Use `currentColor` for fill/stroke
- Standard sizes: 16px, 20px, 24px

## Accessibility
- All images need alt text
- Interactive elements need focus states
- Use semantic HTML elements
- ARIA labels for icon-only buttons
- Respect prefers-reduced-motion

## Performance
- Lazy load images below fold
- Defer non-critical JS
- Critical CSS inline
- Optimize SVGs
- Use native lazy loading

## File Naming
- Lowercase with hyphens: `section-header.css`
- Icons prefix: `icon-{name}.liquid`
- Sections: `{name}.liquid`
- Templates: `{name}.json`
